actions.message:
**:popcorn:Fun:popcorn:**
``g!Slap [@user] - You Slap Mentioned Player

g!Pepe - Send you Pepe with emojis
g!Joke - Send you random joke
g!Meme - Send you random meme
g!CatFacts - Send you Cat Facts
g!CatImages - Send you Cat Image
g!PandaImages - Send you IPanda Image
g!DogImages - Send you Dog Image
g!DogFacts - Send you Dog Facts
g!Lenny - Send you Lenny Faces
g!Color - Send you Random Color
g!Emoji - Send you Random Emoji
g!ChuckNoris - Send you Chuck Noris Joke
g!Randomnumber - Send You Random Number From 1 To 10
g!Kill [@user] - Kill Player
g!Shot [@user] -  Shot Player 
g!Tiny [Text] - Make Tiny/Small Writed Text
g!FakeMsg [@user] [Text] - Send Message As Player ``

**:gear:Moderation:gear:**
``g!Clear - Deleting Messages | For Example !Clear 10
g!Kick [@user] - Kicking Player
g!Ban [@user] - Banning Player
g!Mute [@user] - Muting Player
g!Warn [@user] [reason] - Warning Player 
g!SetGame - Set Bot Game
g!SetStatus - Set Bot Status
g!Prefix [prefix] - Change Bot Prefix
g!Unmute [@user] - Unmuting Muted Player
g!SetListening [text] - Set Listening Writed Text
g!SetWatching [text] - Set Watching writed text
g!SetNick [Nickname] - Change Bot Nickname``

**:books:Information:books:**
``g!Support - Send you link for support discord server
g!Invite - Bot Will Send You Link For Invite
g!Ping - Show your Ping 
g!ServerInfo - Show Server Info
g!Staff - Show staff/team of Bot``

Change your servers prefix by doing %prefix%prefix [prefix] and the bot will respond using that.

The prefix can be anything, it doesn't just have to be a symbol!
